# install packages
ipak <- function(pkg){
  new.pkg <- pkg[!(pkg %in% installed.packages()[, "Package"])]
  if(length(new.pkg)) install.packages(new.pkg, dependencies = TRUE)
  sapply(pkg, require, character.only = TRUE)
}

packages <- c("tidyverse", "tuneR", "signal", "seewave")

Define spiky signal smoother function

spikySignalSmoother = function(spikySignal = y, sampFreq = sampFreq, freqOfInterest = 3){
  # Makes a smooth waveform with the same frequency as
  # the spiky signal
  #
  # Args:
  #   spikySignal: Spiky signal to be smoothed
  #   sampFreq: The sampling frequency of the spiky signal
  #   freqOfInterest: A rough guess at the minimum frequency you're interested in resolving.
  #     If you guess too below the frequency of interest, then you won't get a smooth waveform. 
  #     If you guess too high, then you also won't get a smooth waveform.
  #
  # Returns:
  #   A smooth waveform with the same length as the original spiky signal
  
  periodForFOI = sampFreq / freqOfInterest
  filtSize = 4 * periodForFOI
  
  # defineFilter
  gaussianFilter =  dnorm(x = seq(-4, 4, length.out =  filtSize))
  filteredData = stats::filter(x=(spikySignal), filt = gaussianFilter, circular = TRUE)
  
  # rescale
  scaledFilteredData <- (filteredData-min(filteredData))/(max(filteredData)-min(filteredData)) * 2 - 1
  
  # warning if returned waveform is not smooth
  deriv <- diff(scaledFilteredData)
  if(max(abs(deriv)) > 0.5){
    warning("Returned wave may not be smooth. Try increasing freqOfInterest to be higher than signal frequency")
  }
  else if(sum(deriv == 0) / length(deriv) > 0.1 ){
    warning("Returned wave may not be smooth. Try decreasing freqOfInterest")
  }
  
  return(scaledFilteredData)
}

spikySignalSmoother_rollingMean = function(spikySignal = y, sampFreq = sampFreq, freqOfInterest = 3, 
                                           highPassFiltFreq = 50){
  # Makes a smooth waveform with the same frequency as
  # the spiky signal
  #
  # Args:
  #   spikySignal: Spiky signal to be smoothed
  #   sampFreq: The sampling frequency of the spiky signal
  #   freqOfInterest: A rough guess at the minimum frequency you're interested in resolving.
  #
  # Returns:
  #   A smoother signal with the same length as the original spiky signal
  
  periodForFOI = sampFreq / freqOfInterest / 2
  
  # defineFilter
  filteredData <- zoo::rollmean(abs(spikySignal), k = periodForFOI )
  
  # rescale
  scaledFilteredData <- (filteredData-min(filteredData))/(max(filteredData)-min(filteredData)) * 2 - 1
  
  nyqFreq = sampFreq / 2
  
  bf = signal::butter(6, W = highPassFiltFreq / nyqFreq, type = "high")
  filteredData_F <- signal::filtfilt(bf, scaledFilteredData)
  
  return(filteredData_F)
}

highpass filter (pass high frequencies and attenuate low frequencies)

w1 <- sine(440, duration = 0.5, xunit = "time")
w2 <- sine(1000, duration = 0.5, xunit = "time")

# combine
w11 <- prepComb(w1, where = "end")
w22 <- prepComb(w2, where = "start")
combWave <- bind(w11, w22)
# listen(combWave)


#combWave <- Wave(rnorm(44100 / 2), samp.rate = 44100, bit = 16)

spectro(combWave)

# highpass filter Removes waves below a threshold
nyqFreq = combWave@samp.rate / 2

# 100 Hz is X * nyqFreq

# W is % of nyquist frequency
# for example 0.5 means a frequency of 22050 / 2 cutoff, since 22050
# is the nyquist frequency
HzCutoff = 700


bf = signal::butter(10, W = HzCutoff / nyqFreq, type = "high")
b1 <- signal::filtfilt(bf, combWave@left)
dev.off()

# load sound
w1 <- readWave(wavFle) #, from = 3, to = 3.4, units = "seconds")
sampRate = w1@samp.rate
nyqFreq = sampRate / 2

# first highpass filter
highpassFreq = 10000 # hz

# convert to mono
if(w1@stereo){
  w1 <- mono(w1, "left")
}

w2 <- w1@left

plot(w2, type = 'l')

# high-pass filter
bf = signal::butter(6, W = highpassFreq / nyqFreq, type = "high")
b1 <- signal::filtfilt(bf, w2)
## listen(b1, f = sampRate)

plot(b1, type = 'l')

# convert spiky signal to smooth signal

b2 <- spikySignalSmoother_rollingMean(b1, sampFreq = sampRate, freqOfInterest = 300)

plot(b2, type = "l")

# view fundamental frequency over time: 
# with 50% overlap between successive sliding windows, time zoom and 
# amplitude filter (threshold)
# overlaid on a spectrogram
spectro(b2, f=sampRate, ovlp=50, zp=16, wl = 2**13,
        scale=FALSE, palette=reverse.gray.colors.2, flim = c(0, 1))
fundPts = fund(b2,
               f = sampRate, ovlp = 0.75, wl = 2**13,
               fmax = 500,
               threshold = 1, 
               plot = FALSE) %>%
          as.data.frame()
